  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 6c3d464ededf4134c847abc300a02088, type: 3}
  m_Name: JOB
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  <Name>k__BackingField: Job
  fancyName: 
  nickname: job
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job and His Family in Uz'
      title: Job and His Family in Uz
      number: 1
      content: 'There was a man in the land of Uz, whose name was  Job; and that
        man was blameless and upright, and one who feared God and shunned evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And seven sons and three daughters were born to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Also, his possessions were seven thousand sheep, three thousand camels,
        five hundred yoke of oxen, five hundred female donkeys, and a very large
        household, so that this man was the greatest of all the people of the East.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And his sons would go and feast in  their houses, each on his appointed
        day, and would send and invite their three sisters to eat and drink with
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: "5: Satan Attacks Job\u2019s Character"
      title: "Satan Attacks Job\u2019s Character"
      number: 5
      content: "So it was, when the days of feasting had run their course, that Job
        would send and sanctify them, and he would rise early in the morning and
        offer burnt offerings according  to the number of them all. For Job said,
        \u201CIt may be that my sons have sinned and cursed God in their hearts.\u201D
        Thus Job did regularly."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now there was a day when the sons of God came to present themselves
        before the Lord, and Satan also came among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the Lord said to Satan, \u201CFrom where do you come?\u201DSo
        Satan answered the Lord and said, \u201CFrom going to and fro on the earth,
        and from walking back and forth on it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the Lord said to Satan, \u201CHave you considered My servant
        Job, that there  is none like him on the earth, a blameless and upright man,
        one who fears God and shuns evil?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Satan answered the Lord and said, \u201CDoes Job fear God for
        nothing? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Have You not made a hedge around him, around his household, and around
        all that he has on every side? You have blessed the work of his hands, and
        his possessions have increased in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But now, stretch out Your hand and touch all that he has, and he
        will surely curse You to Your face!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Job Loses His Property and Children'
      title: Job Loses His Property and Children
      number: 12
      content: "And the Lord said to Satan, \u201CBehold, all that he has is in your
        power; only do not lay a hand on his person.\u201DSo Satan went out from
        the presence of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now there was a day when his sons and daughters were eating and drinking
        wine in their oldest brother\u2019s house; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and a messenger came to Job and said, \u201CThe oxen were plowing
        and the donkeys feeding beside them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "when the Sabeans raided them and took them away\u2014indeed they
        have killed the servants with the edge of the sword; and I alone have escaped
        to tell you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "While he was still speaking, another also came and said, \u201CThe
        fire of God fell from heaven and burned up the sheep and the servants, and
        consumed them; and I alone have escaped to tell you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "While he was still speaking, another also came and said, \u201CThe
        Chaldeans formed three bands, raided the camels and took them away, yes,
        and killed the servants with the edge of the sword; and I alone have escaped
        to tell you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "While he was still speaking, another also came and said, \u201CYour
        sons and daughters were eating and drinking wine in their oldest brother\u2019s
        house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and suddenly a great wind came from across the wilderness and struck
        the four corners of the house, and it fell on the young people, and they
        are dead; and I alone have escaped to tell you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Job arose, tore his robe, and shaved his head; and he fell to
        the ground and worshiped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he said:\u201CNaked I came from my mother\u2019s womb,And naked
        shall I return there.The Lord  gave, and the Lord has taken away;Blessed
        be the name of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: In all this Job did not sin nor charge God with wrong.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Satan Attacks Job\u2019s Health"
      title: "Satan Attacks Job\u2019s Health"
      number: 1
      content: 'Again there was a day when the sons of God came to present themselves
        before the Lord, and Satan came also among them to present himself before
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said to Satan, \u201CFrom where do you come?\u201DSatan
        answered the Lord and said, \u201CFrom going to and fro on the earth, and
        from walking back and forth on it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said to Satan, \u201CHave you considered My servant
        Job, that there  is none like him on the earth, a blameless and upright man,
        one who fears God and shuns evil? And still he holds fast to his integrity,
        although you incited Me against him, to destroy him without cause.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Satan answered the Lord and said, \u201CSkin for skin! Yes, all
        that a man has he will give for his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But stretch out Your hand now, and touch his bone and his flesh,
        and he will surely curse You to Your face!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the Lord said to Satan, \u201CBehold, he is in your hand, but
        spare his life.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Satan went out from the presence of the Lord, and struck Job with
        painful boils from the sole of his foot to the crown of his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And he took for himself a potsherd with which to scrape himself while
        he sat in the midst of the ashes.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then his wife said to him, \u201CDo you still hold fast to your integrity?
        Curse God and die!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Job\u2019s Three Friends"
      title: "Job\u2019s Three Friends"
      number: 10
      content: "But he said to her, \u201CYou speak as one of the foolish women speaks.
        Shall we indeed accept good from God, and shall we not accept adversity?\u201D
        In all this Job did not sin with his lips."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when Job\u2019s three friends heard of all this adversity that
        had come upon him, each one came from his own place\u2014Eliphaz the Temanite,
        Bildad the Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite. For they had made an appointment
        together to come and mourn with him, and to comfort him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when they raised their eyes from afar, and did not recognize
        him, they lifted their voices and wept; and each one tore his robe and sprinkled
        dust on his head toward heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So they sat down with him on the ground seven days and seven nights,
        and no one spoke a word to him, for they saw that his grief was very great.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Deplores His Birth'
      title: Job Deplores His Birth
      number: 1
      content: After this Job opened his mouth and cursed the day of his birth.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Job spoke, and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CMay the day perish on which I was born,And the night in  which
        it was said,\u2018A male child is conceived.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: May that day be darkness;May God above not seek it,Nor the light shine
        upon it.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: May darkness and the shadow of death claim it;May a cloud settle on
        it;May the blackness of the day terrify it.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: As  for that night, may darkness seize it;May it not rejoice among
        the days of the year,May it not come into the number of the months.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Oh, may that night be barren!May no joyful shout come into it!
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: May those curse it who curse the day,Those who are ready to arouse
        Leviathan.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: May the stars of its morning be dark;May it look for light, but have
        none,And not see the dawning of the day;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Because it did not shut up the doors of my mother\u2019s womb,Nor
        hide sorrow from my eyes."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhy did I not die at birth?Why did I not perish when I came
        from the womb?"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Why did the knees receive me?Or why the breasts, that I should nurse?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For now I would have lain still and been quiet,I would have been asleep;Then
        I would have been at rest
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: With kings and counselors of the earth,Who built ruins for themselves,
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Or with princes who had gold,Who filled their houses with silver;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Or why was I not hidden like a stillborn child,Like infants who never
        saw light?
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: There the wicked cease from troubling,And there the weary are at rest.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: There the prisoners rest together;They do not hear the voice of the
        oppressor.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The small and great are there,And the servant is free from his master.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhy is light given to him who is in misery,And life to the
        bitter of soul,"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Who long for death, but it does not come,And search for it more than
        hidden treasures;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Who rejoice exceedingly,And are glad when they can find the grave?
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Why  is  light  given to a man whose way is hidden,And whom God has
        hedged in?
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: For my sighing comes before I eat,And my groanings pour out like water.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: For the thing I greatly feared has come upon me,And what I dreaded
        has happened to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I am not at ease, nor am I quiet;I have no rest, for trouble comes.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz: Job Has Sinned'
      title: 'Eliphaz: Job Has Sinned'
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf one attempts a word with you, will you become weary?But
        who can withhold himself from speaking?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Surely you have instructed many,And you have strengthened weak hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Your words have upheld him who was stumbling,And you have strengthened
        the feeble knees;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But now it comes upon you, and you are weary;It touches you, and you
        are troubled.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Is not your reverence your confidence?And the integrity of your ways
        your hope?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CRemember now, who ever perished being innocent?Or where were
        the upright ever cut off?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Even as I have seen,Those who plow iniquityAnd sow trouble reap the
        same.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: By the blast of God they perish,And by the breath of His anger they
        are consumed.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The roaring of the lion,The voice of the fierce lion,And the teeth
        of the young lions are broken.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The old lion perishes for lack of prey,And the cubs of the lioness
        are scattered.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CNow a word was secretly brought to me,And my ear received a
        whisper of it."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: In disquieting thoughts from the visions of the night,When deep sleep
        falls on men,
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Fear came upon me, and trembling,Which made all my bones shake.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then a spirit passed before my face;The hair on my body stood up.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It stood still,But I could not discern its appearance.A form was
        before my eyes;There  was silence;Then I heard a voice saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Can a mortal be more righteous than God?Can a man be more pure
        than his Maker?"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: If He puts no trust in His servants,If He charges His angels with
        error,
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: How much more those who dwell in houses of clay,Whose foundation is
        in the dust,Who are crushed before a moth?
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: They are broken in pieces from morning till evening;They perish forever,
        with no one regarding.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Does not their own excellence go away?They die, even without wisdom.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz: Job Is Chastened by God'
      title: 'Eliphaz: Job Is Chastened by God'
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CCall out now;Is there anyone who will answer you?And to which
        of the holy ones will you turn?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For wrath kills a foolish man,And envy slays a simple one.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I have seen the foolish taking root,But suddenly I cursed his dwelling
        place.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: His sons are far from safety,They are crushed in the gate,And there 
        is no deliverer.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Because the hungry eat up his harvest,Taking it even from the thorns,And
        a snare snatches their substance.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For affliction does not come from the dust,Nor does trouble spring
        from the ground;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Yet man is born to trouble,As the sparks fly upward.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut as for me, I would seek God,And to God I would commit my
        cause\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Who does great things, and unsearchable,Marvelous things without number.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He gives rain on the earth,And sends waters on the fields.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He sets on high those who are lowly,And those who mourn are lifted
        to safety.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He frustrates the devices of the crafty,So that their hands cannot
        carry out their plans.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He catches the wise in their own craftiness,And the counsel of the
        cunning comes quickly upon them.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They meet with darkness in the daytime,And grope at noontime as in
        the night.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But He saves the needy from the sword,From the mouth of the mighty,And
        from their hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So the poor have hope,And injustice shuts her mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBehold, happy is the man whom God corrects;Therefore do not
        despise the chastening of the Almighty."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For He bruises, but He binds up;He wounds, but His hands make whole.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He shall deliver you in six troubles,Yes, in seven no evil shall touch
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: In famine He shall redeem you from death,And in war from the power
        of the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: You shall be hidden from the scourge of the tongue,And you shall not
        be afraid of destruction when it comes.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: You shall laugh at destruction and famine,And you shall not be afraid
        of the beasts of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For you shall have a covenant with the stones of the field,And the
        beasts of the field shall be at peace with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: You shall know that your tent is in peace;You shall visit your dwelling
        and find nothing amiss.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: You shall also know that your descendants shall  be many,And your
        offspring like the grass of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: You shall come to the grave at a full age,As a sheaf of grain ripens
        in its season.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Behold, this we have searched out;It is true.Hear it, and know for
        yourself.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job: My Complaint Is Just'
      title: 'Job: My Complaint Is Just'
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COh, that my grief were fully weighed,And my calamity laid with
        it on the scales!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For then it would be heavier than the sand of the sea\u2014Therefore
        my words have been rash."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For the arrows of the Almighty are within me;My spirit drinks in their
        poison;The terrors of God are arrayed against me.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Does the wild donkey bray when it has grass,Or does the ox low over
        its fodder?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Can flavorless food be eaten without salt?Or is there any taste in
        the white of an egg?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: My soul refuses to touch them;They are as loathsome food to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COh, that I might have my request,That God would grant me the
        thing that I long for!"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: That it would please God to crush me,That He would loose His hand
        and cut me off!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then I would still have comfort;Though in anguish I would exult,He
        will not spare;For I have not concealed the words of the Holy One.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhat strength do I have, that I should hope?And what is my
        end, that I should prolong my life?"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Is my strength the strength of stones?Or is my flesh bronze?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Is my help not within me?And is success driven from me?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTo him who is afflicted, kindness should  be  shown by his
        friend,Even though he forsakes the fear of the Almighty."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: My brothers have dealt deceitfully like a brook,Like the streams of
        the brooks that pass away,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Which are dark because of the ice,And into which the snow vanishes.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: When it is warm, they cease to flow;When it is hot, they vanish from
        their place.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The paths of their way turn aside,They go nowhere and perish.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The caravans of Tema look,The travelers of Sheba hope for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: They are disappointed because they were confident;They come there
        and are confused.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For now you are nothing,You see terror and are afraid.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Did I ever say, \u2018Bring something to me\u2019?Or, \u2018Offer
        a bribe for me from your wealth\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Or, \u2018Deliver me from the enemy\u2019s hand\u2019?Or, \u2018Redeem
        me from the hand of oppressors\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CTeach me, and I will hold my tongue;Cause me to understand
        wherein I have erred."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: How forceful are right words!But what does your arguing prove?
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Do you intend to rebuke my words,And the speeches of a desperate one,
        which  are as wind?
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Yes, you overwhelm the fatherless,And you undermine your friend.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Now therefore, be pleased to look at me;For I would never lie to your
        face.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Yield now, let there be no injustice!Yes, concede, my righteousness
        still stands!
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Is there injustice on my tongue?Cannot my taste discern the unsavory?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job: My Suffering Is Comfortless'
      title: 'Job: My Suffering Is Comfortless'
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CIs  there not a time of hard service for man on earth?Are 
        not his days also like the days of a hired man?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Like a servant who earnestly desires the shade,And like a hired man
        who eagerly looks for his wages,
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: So I have been allotted months of futility,And wearisome nights have
        been appointed to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When I lie down, I say, \u2018When shall I arise,And the night be
        ended?\u2019For I have had my fill of tossing till dawn."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: My flesh is caked with worms and dust,My skin is cracked and breaks
        out afresh.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CMy days are swifter than a weaver\u2019s shuttle,And are spent
        without hope."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Oh, remember that my life is a breath!My eye will never again see
        good.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The eye of him who sees me will see me no more;While your eyes are
        upon me, I shall no longer be.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: As the cloud disappears and vanishes away,So he who goes down to the
        grave does not come up.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He shall never return to his house,Nor shall his place know him anymore.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will not restrain my mouth;I will speak in the
        anguish of my spirit;I will complain in the bitterness of my soul."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Am I a sea, or a sea serpent,That You set a guard over me?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When I say, \u2018My bed will comfort me,My couch will ease my complaint,\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then You scare me with dreamsAnd terrify me with visions,
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So that my soul chooses stranglingAnd death rather than my body.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I loathe my  life;I would not live forever.Let me alone,For my days
        are  but a breath.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CWhat  is man, that You should exalt him,That You should set
        Your heart on him,"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: That You should visit him every morning,And test him every moment?
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: How long?Will You not look away from me,And let me alone till I swallow
        my saliva?
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Have I sinned?What have I done to You, O watcher of men?Why have You
        set me as Your target,So that I am a burden to myself?
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Why then do You not pardon my transgression,And take away my iniquity?For
        now I will lie down in the dust,And You will seek me diligently,But I will
        no longer be.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad: Job Should Repent'
      title: 'Bildad: Job Should Repent'
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you speak these things,And the words of your
        mouth be  like a strong wind?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Does God subvert judgment?Or does the Almighty pervert justice?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: If your sons have sinned against Him,He has cast them away for their
        transgression.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: If you would earnestly seek GodAnd make your supplication to the Almighty,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: If you were pure and upright,Surely now He would awake for you,And
        prosper your rightful dwelling place.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Though your beginning was small,Yet your latter end would increase
        abundantly.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CFor inquire, please, of the former age,And consider the things
        discovered by their fathers;"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For we were  born yesterday, and know nothing,Because our days on
        earth are a shadow.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Will they not teach you and tell you,And utter words from their heart?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CCan the papyrus grow up without a marsh?Can the reeds flourish
        without water?"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: While it is yet green and not cut down,It withers before any other
        plant.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So are the paths of all who forget God;And the hope of the hypocrite
        shall perish,
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Whose confidence shall be cut off,And whose trust is a spider\u2019s
        web."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He leans on his house, but it does not stand.He holds it fast, but
        it does not endure.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He grows green in the sun,And his branches spread out in his garden.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: His roots wrap around the rock heap,And look for a place in the stones.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If he is destroyed from his place,Then it will deny him, saying,
        \u2018I have not seen you.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CBehold, this is the joy of His way,And out of the earth others
        will grow."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Behold, God will not cast away the blameless,Nor will He uphold the
        evildoers.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He will yet fill your mouth with laughing,And your lips with rejoicing.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Those who hate you will be clothed with shame,And the dwelling place
        of the wicked will come to nothing.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job: There Is No Mediator'
      title: 'Job: There Is No Mediator'
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTruly I know it  is so,But how can a man be righteous before
        God?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: If one wished to contend with Him,He could not answer Him one time
        out of a thousand.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: God  is wise in heart and mighty in strength.Who has hardened himself
        against Him and prospered?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He removes the mountains, and they do not knowWhen He overturns them
        in His anger;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He shakes the earth out of its place,And its pillars tremble;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He commands the sun, and it does not rise;He seals off the stars;
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He alone spreads out the heavens,And treads on the waves of the sea;
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He made the Bear, Orion, and the Pleiades,And the chambers of the
        south;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He does great things past finding out,Yes, wonders without number.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: If He goes by me, I do not see Him;If He moves past, I do not perceive
        Him;
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If He takes away, who can hinder Him?Who can say to Him, \u2018What
        are You doing?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: God will not withdraw His anger,The allies of the proud lie prostrate
        beneath Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CHow then can I answer Him,And choose my words to  reason with
        Him?"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: For though I were righteous, I could not answer Him;I would beg mercy
        of my Judge.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: If I called and He answered me,I would not believe that He was listening
        to my voice.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For He crushes me with a tempest,And multiplies my wounds without
        cause.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He will not allow me to catch my breath,But fills me with bitterness.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: If it  is  a  matter of strength, indeed He  is strong;And if of justice,
        who will appoint my day in  court?
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Though I were righteous, my own mouth would condemn me;Though I were
        blameless, it would prove me perverse.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI am blameless, yet I do not know myself;I despise my life."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "It is all one thing;Therefore I say, \u2018He destroys the blameless
        and the wicked.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: If the scourge slays suddenly,He laughs at the plight of the innocent.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The earth is given into the hand of the wicked.He covers the faces
        of its judges.If it is not He, who else could it be?
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CNow my days are swifter than a runner;They flee away, they
        see no good."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: They pass by like swift ships,Like an eagle swooping on its prey.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If I say, \u2018I will forget my complaint,I will put off my sad
        face and wear a smile,\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: I am afraid of all my sufferings;I know that You will not hold me
        innocent.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: If I am condemned,Why then do I labor in vain?
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: If I wash myself with snow water,And cleanse my hands with soap,
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Yet You will plunge me into the pit,And my own clothes will abhor
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CFor He  is not a man, as I am,That I may answer Him,And  that
        we should go to court together."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Nor is there any mediator between us,Who may lay his hand on us both.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Let Him take His rod away from me,And do not let dread of Him terrify
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Then I would speak and not fear Him,But it is not so with me.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job: I Would Plead with God'
      title: 'Job: I Would Plead with God'
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMy soul loathes my life;I will give free course to my complaint,I
        will speak in the bitterness of my soul."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I will say to God, \u2018Do not condemn me;Show me why You contend
        with me."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Does  it seem good to You that You should oppress,That You should
        despise the work of Your hands,And smile on the counsel of the wicked?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Do You have eyes of flesh?Or do You see as man sees?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Are Your days like the days of a mortal man?Are Your years like the
        days of a mighty man,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: That You should seek for my iniquityAnd search out my sin,
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Although You know that I am not wicked,And there  is no one who can
        deliver from Your hand?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018Your hands have made me and fashioned me,An intricate unity;Yet
        You would destroy me."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Remember, I pray, that You have made me like clay.And will You turn
        me into dust again?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Did You not pour me out like milk,And curdle me like cheese,
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Clothe me with skin and flesh,And knit me together with bones and
        sinews?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: You have granted me life and favor,And Your care has preserved my
        spirit.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u2018And these things You have hidden in Your heart;I know that
        this was with You:"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: If I sin, then You mark me,And will not acquit me of my iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: If I am wicked, woe to me;Even if I am righteous, I cannot lift up
        my head.I  am full of disgrace;See my misery!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: If my  head is exalted,You hunt me like a fierce lion,And again You
        show Yourself awesome against me.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: You renew Your witnesses against me,And increase Your indignation
        toward me;Changes and war are ever with me.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018Why then have You brought me out of the womb?Oh, that I had
        perished and no eye had seen me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: I would have been as though I had not been.I would have been carried
        from the womb to the grave.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Are not my days few?Cease! Leave me alone, that I may take a little
        comfort,
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Before I go to  the  place  from  which I shall not return,To the
        land of darkness and the shadow of death,
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A land as dark as darkness itself,As the shadow of death, without
        any order,Where even the light is like darkness.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zophar Urges Job to Repent'
      title: Zophar Urges Job to Repent
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShould not the multitude of words be answered?And should a
        man full of talk be vindicated?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Should your empty talk make men hold their peace?And when you mock,
        should no one rebuke you?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For you have said,\u2018My doctrine is pure,And I am clean in your
        eyes.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But oh, that God would speak,And open His lips against you,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: That He would show you the secrets of wisdom!For they  would double
        your prudence.Know therefore that God exacts from youLess than your iniquity
        deserves.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CCan you search out the deep things of God?Can you find out
        the limits of the Almighty?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They  are higher than heaven\u2014 what can you do?Deeper than Sheol\u2014
        what can you know?"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Their measure is longer than the earthAnd broader than the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf He passes by, imprisons, and gathers to  judgment,Then who
        can hinder Him?"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For He knows deceitful men;He sees wickedness also.Will He not then
        consider it?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For an empty-headed man will be wise,When a wild donkey\u2019s colt
        is born a man."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf you would prepare your heart,And stretch out your hands
        toward Him;"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: If iniquity were in your hand, and  you put it far away,And would
        not let wickedness dwell in your tents;
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then surely you could lift up your face without spot;Yes, you could
        be steadfast, and not fear;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Because you would forget your misery,And remember it as waters that 
        have passed away,
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And your life would be brighter than noonday.Though you were dark,
        you would be like the morning.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And you would be secure, because there is hope;Yes, you would dig
        around  you, and  take your rest in safety.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: You would also lie down, and no one would make you afraid;Yes, many
        would court your favor.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the eyes of the wicked will fail,And they shall not escape,And
        their hope\u2014loss of life!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Answers His Critics'
      title: Job Answers His Critics
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNo doubt you are the people,And wisdom will die with you!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But I have understanding as well as you;I am not inferior to you.Indeed,
        who does not know such things as these?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI am one mocked by his friends,Who called on God, and He answered
        him,The just and blameless who  is ridiculed."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A lamp is despised in the thought of one who is at ease;It  is made
        ready for those whose feet slip.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The tents of robbers prosper,And those who provoke God are secure\u2014In
        what God provides by His hand."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut now ask the beasts, and they will teach you;And the birds
        of the air, and they will tell you;"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Or speak to the earth, and it will teach you;And the fish of the sea
        will explain to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Who among all these does not knowThat the hand of the Lord has done
        this,
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: In whose hand is the life of every living thing,And the breath of
        all mankind?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Does not the ear test wordsAnd the mouth taste its food?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Wisdom is with aged men,And with length of days, understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWith Him are  wisdom and strength,He has counsel and understanding."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: If He breaks a  thing down, it cannot be rebuilt;If He imprisons a
        man, there can be no release.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: If He withholds the waters, they dry up;If He sends them out, they
        overwhelm the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: With Him are strength and prudence.The deceived and the deceiver are
        His.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He leads counselors away plundered,And makes fools of the judges.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He loosens the bonds of kings,And binds their waist with a belt.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He leads princes away plundered,And overthrows the mighty.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He deprives the trusted ones of speech,And takes away the discernment
        of the elders.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He pours contempt on princes,And disarms the mighty.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He uncovers deep things out of darkness,And brings the shadow of death
        to light.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He makes nations great, and destroys them;He enlarges nations, and
        guides them.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He takes away the understanding of the chiefs of the people of the
        earth,And makes them wander in a pathless wilderness.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: They grope in the dark without light,And He makes them stagger like
        a drunken man.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBehold, my eye has seen all this,My ear has heard and understood
        it."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: What you know, I also know;I am not inferior to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But I would speak to the Almighty,And I desire to reason with God.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But you forgers of lies,You are all worthless physicians.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Oh, that you would be silent,And it would be your wisdom!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Now hear my reasoning,And heed the pleadings of my lips.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Will you speak wickedly for God,And talk deceitfully for Him?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Will you show partiality for Him?Will you contend for God?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Will it be well when He searches you out?Or can you mock Him as one
        mocks a man?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He will surely rebuke youIf you secretly show partiality.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Will not His excellence make you afraid,And the dread of Him fall
        upon you?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Your platitudes are proverbs of ashes,Your defenses are defenses of
        clay.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CHold your peace with me, and let me speak,Then let come on
        me what may!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Why do I take my flesh in my teeth,And put my life in my hands?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Though He slay me, yet will I trust Him.Even so, I will defend my
        own ways before Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He also shall be my salvation,For a hypocrite could not come before
        Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Listen carefully to my speech,And to my declaration with your ears.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: See now, I have prepared my case,I know that I shall be vindicated.
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Job\u2019s Despondent Prayer"
      title: "Job\u2019s Despondent Prayer"
      number: 19
      content: Who is he who will contend with me?If now I hold my tongue, I perish.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201COnly two things do not do to me,Then I will not hide myself
        from You:"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Withdraw Your hand far from me,And let not the dread of You make me
        afraid.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then call, and I will answer;Or let me speak, then You respond to
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: How many are my iniquities and sins?Make me know my transgression
        and my sin.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Why do You hide Your face,And regard me as Your enemy?
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Will You frighten a leaf driven to and fro?And will You pursue dry
        stubble?
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For You write bitter things against me,And make me inherit the iniquities
        of my youth.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: You put my feet in the stocks,And watch closely all my paths.You set
        a limit for the soles of my feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CMan decays like a rotten thing,Like a garment that is moth-eaten."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMan who  is born of womanIs of few days and full of trouble."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He comes forth like a flower and fades away;He flees like a shadow
        and does not continue.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And do You open Your eyes on such a one,And bring me to judgment with
        Yourself?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Who can bring a clean thing out of an unclean?No one!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Since his days are determined,The number of his months is with You;You
        have appointed his limits, so that he cannot pass.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Look away from him that he may rest,Till like a hired man he finishes
        his day.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor there is hope for a tree,If it is cut down, that it will
        sprout again,And that its tender shoots will not cease."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Though its root may grow old in the earth,And its stump may die in
        the ground,
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Yet at the scent of water it will budAnd bring forth branches like
        a plant.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But man dies and is laid away;Indeed he breathes his lastAnd where
        is  he?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: As water disappears from the sea,And a river becomes parched and dries
        up,
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: So man lies down and does not rise.Till the heavens are no more,They
        will not awakeNor be roused from their sleep.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201COh, that You would hide me in the grave,That You would conceal
        me until Your wrath is past,That You would appoint me a set time, and remember
        me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: If a man dies, shall he live again?All the days of my hard service
        I will wait,Till my change comes.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You shall call, and I will answer You;You shall desire the work of
        Your hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For now You number my steps,But do not watch over my sin.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: My transgression is sealed up in a bag,And You cover my iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut as a mountain falls and crumbles away,And as a rock is
        moved from its place;"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: As water wears away stones,And  as torrents wash away the soil of
        the earth;So You destroy the hope of man.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You prevail forever against him, and he passes on;You change his countenance
        and send him away.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: His sons come to honor, and he does not know it;They are brought low,
        and he does not perceive it.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But his flesh will be in pain over it,And his soul will mourn over
        it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz Accuses Job of Folly'
      title: Eliphaz Accuses Job of Folly
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShould a wise man answer with empty knowledge,And fill himself
        with the east wind?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Should he reason with unprofitable talk,Or by speeches with which
        he can do no good?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Yes, you cast off fear,And restrain prayer before God.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For your iniquity teaches your mouth,And you choose the tongue of
        the crafty.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Your own mouth condemns you, and not I;Yes, your own lips testify
        against you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAre you the first man who was born?Or were you made before
        the hills?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Have you heard the counsel of God?Do you limit wisdom to yourself?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: What do you know that we do not know?What do you understand that is
        not in us?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Both the gray-haired and the aged are among us,Much older than your
        father.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Are the consolations of God too small for you,And the word spoken
        gently with you?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Why does your heart carry you away,And what do your eyes wink at,
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: That you turn your spirit against God,And let such words go out of
        your mouth?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhat  is man, that he could be pure?And he  who  is born of
        a woman, that he could be righteous?"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: If God puts no trust in His saints,And the heavens are not pure in
        His sight,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: How much less man, who  is abominable and filthy,Who drinks iniquity
        like water!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CI will tell you, hear me;What I have seen I will declare,"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: What wise men have told,Not hiding anything  received  from their
        fathers,
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'To whom alone the land was given,And no alien passed among them:'
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The wicked man writhes with pain all his days,And the number of years
        is hidden from the oppressor.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Dreadful sounds are in his ears;In prosperity the destroyer comes
        upon him.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He does not believe that he will return from darkness,For a sword
        is waiting for him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He wanders about for bread, saying, \u2018Where is  it?\u2019He knows
        that a day of darkness is ready at his hand."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Trouble and anguish make him afraid;They overpower him, like a king
        ready for battle.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: For he stretches out his hand against God,And acts defiantly against
        the Almighty,
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Running stubbornly against HimWith his strong, embossed shield.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CThough he has covered his face with his fatness,And made his
        waist heavy with fat,"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: He dwells in desolate cities,In houses which no one inhabits,Which
        are destined to become ruins.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: He will not be rich,Nor will his wealth continue,Nor will his possessions
        overspread the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: He will not depart from darkness;The flame will dry out his branches,And
        by the breath of His mouth he will go away.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Let him not trust in futile things, deceiving himself,For futility
        will be his reward.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: It will be accomplished before his time,And his branch will not be
        green.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: He will shake off his unripe grape like a vine,And cast off his blossom
        like an olive tree.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: For the company of hypocrites will  be barren,And fire will consume
        the tents of bribery.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "They conceive trouble and bring forth futility;Their womb prepares
        deceit.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Reproaches His Pitiless Friends'
      title: Job Reproaches His Pitiless Friends
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI have heard many such things;Miserable comforters are you
        all!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Shall words of wind have an end?Or what provokes you that you answer?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I also could speak as you do,If your soul were in my soul\u2019s
        place.I could heap up words against you,And shake my head at you;"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But I would strengthen you with my mouth,And the comfort of my lips
        would relieve your  grief.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThough I speak, my grief is not relieved;And if I remain silent,
        how am I eased?"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But now He has worn me out;You have made desolate all my company.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: You have shriveled me up,And it is a witness against  me;My leanness
        rises up against meAnd bears witness to my face.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He tears me in His wrath, and hates me;He gnashes at me with His teeth;My
        adversary sharpens His gaze on me.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: They gape at me with their mouth,They strike me reproachfully on the
        cheek,They gather together against me.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: God has delivered me to the ungodly,And turned me over to the hands
        of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: I was at ease, but He has shattered me;He also has taken me by my
        neck, and shaken me to pieces;He has set me up for His target,
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: His archers surround me.He pierces my heart and does not pity;He pours
        out my gall on the ground.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He breaks me with wound upon wound;He runs at me like a warrior.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CI have sewn sackcloth over my skin,And laid my head in the
        dust."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: My face is flushed from weeping,And on my eyelids is the shadow of
        death;
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Although no violence is in my hands,And my prayer is pure.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CO earth, do not cover my blood,And let my cry have no resting
        place!"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Surely even now my witness is in heaven,And my evidence is on high.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: My friends scorn me;My eyes pour out tears to God.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Oh, that one might plead for a man with God,As a man pleads for his
        neighbor!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For when a few years are finished,I shall go the way of no return.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Prays for Relief'
      title: Job Prays for Relief
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CMy spirit is broken,My days are extinguished,The grave is 
        ready for me."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Are not mockers with me?And does not my eye dwell on their provocation?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CNow put down a pledge for me with Yourself.Who is he who  will
        shake hands with me?"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For You have hidden their heart from understanding;Therefore You will
        not exalt them.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He who speaks flattery to his friends,Even the eyes of his children
        will fail.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBut He has made me a byword of the people,And I have become
        one in whose face men spit."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: My eye has also grown dim because of sorrow,And all my members are
        like shadows.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Upright men are astonished at this,And the innocent stirs himself
        up against the hypocrite.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Yet the righteous will hold to his way,And he who has clean hands
        will be stronger and stronger.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CBut please, come back again, all of you,For I shall not find
        one wise man among you."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: My days are past,My purposes are broken off,Even the thoughts of my
        heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They change the night into day;\u2018The light is near,\u2019 they 
        say, in the face of darkness."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: If I wait for the grave as my house,If I make my bed in the darkness,
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "If I say to corruption, \u2018You are my father,\u2019And to the
        worm, \u2018You are my mother and my sister,\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Where then is my hope?As for my hope, who can see it?
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Will they go down to the gates of Sheol?Shall we  have  rest together
        in the dust?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad: The Wicked Are Punished'
      title: 'Bildad: The Wicked Are Punished'
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long till you put an end to words?Gain understanding, and
        afterward we will speak."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Why are we counted as beasts,And regarded as stupid in your sight?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: You who tear yourself in anger,Shall the earth be forsaken for you?Or
        shall the rock be removed from its place?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThe light of the wicked indeed goes out,And the flame of his
        fire does not shine."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The light is dark in his tent,And his lamp beside him is put out.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The steps of his strength are shortened,And his own counsel casts
        him down.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For he is cast into a net by his own feet,And he walks into a snare.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The net takes him by the heel,And  a snare lays hold of him.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: A noose is hidden for him on the ground,And a trap for him in the
        road.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Terrors frighten him on every side,And drive him to his feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: His strength is starved,And destruction is ready at his side.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: It devours patches of his skin;The firstborn of death devours his
        limbs.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He is uprooted from the shelter of his tent,And they parade him before
        the king of terrors.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They dwell in his tent who  are none of his;Brimstone is scattered
        on his dwelling.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: His roots are dried out below,And his branch withers above.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The memory of him perishes from the earth,And he has no name among
        the renowned.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He is driven from light into darkness,And chased out of the world.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He has neither son nor posterity among his people,Nor any remaining
        in his dwellings.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Those in the west are astonished at his day,As those in the east are
        frightened.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Surely such are the dwellings of the wicked,And this is the place
        of  him  who  does not know God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Trusts in His Redeemer'
      title: Job Trusts in His Redeemer
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow long will you torment my soul,And break me in pieces with
        words?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: These ten times you have reproached me;You are not ashamed that you
        have wronged me.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And if indeed I have erred,My error remains with me.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: If indeed you exalt yourselves against me,And plead my disgrace against
        me,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Know then that God has wronged me,And has surrounded me with His net.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf I cry out concerning wrong, I am not heard.If I cry aloud,
        there  is no justice."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He has fenced up my way, so that I cannot pass;And He has set darkness
        in my paths.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He has stripped me of my glory,And taken the crown from my head.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He breaks me down on every side,And I am gone;My hope He has uprooted
        like a tree.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He has also kindled His wrath against me,And He counts me as one 
        of His enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: His troops come togetherAnd build up their road against me;They encamp
        all around my tent.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CHe has removed my brothers far from me,And my acquaintances
        are completely estranged from me."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: My relatives have failed,And my close friends have forgotten me.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Those who dwell in my house, and my maidservants,Count me as a stranger;I
        am an alien in their sight.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I call my servant, but he gives no answer;I beg him with my mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: My breath is offensive to my wife,And I am repulsive to the children
        of my own body.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Even young children despise me;I arise, and they speak against me.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: All my close friends abhor me,And those whom I love have turned against
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: My bone clings to my skin and to my flesh,And I have escaped by the
        skin of my teeth.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CHave pity on me, have pity on me, O you my friends,For the
        hand of God has struck me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Why do you persecute me as God does,And are not satisfied with my
        flesh?
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201COh, that my words were written!Oh, that they were inscribed
        in a book!"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: That they were engraved on a rockWith an iron pen and lead, forever!
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: For I know that my Redeemer lives,And He shall stand at last on the
        earth;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And after my skin is destroyed, this I  know,That in my flesh I shall
        see God,
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Whom I shall see for myself,And my eyes shall behold, and not another.How
        my heart yearns within me!
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "If you should say, \u2018How shall we persecute him?\u2019\u2014Since
        the root of the matter is found in me,"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Be afraid of the sword for yourselves;For wrath brings the punishment
        of the sword,That you may know there  is a judgment.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zophar\u2019s Sermon on the Wicked Man"
      title: "Zophar\u2019s Sermon on the Wicked Man"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Zophar the Naamathite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTherefore my anxious thoughts make me answer,Because of the
        turmoil within me."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I have heard the rebuke that reproaches me,And the spirit of my understanding
        causes me to answer.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CDo you not know this of old,Since man was placed on earth,"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: That the triumphing of the wicked is short,And the joy of the hypocrite
        is but for a moment?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Though his haughtiness mounts up to the heavens,And his head reaches
        to the clouds,
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Yet he will perish forever like his own refuse;Those who have seen
        him will say, \u2018Where is he?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He will fly away like a dream, and not be found;Yes, he will be chased
        away like a vision of the night.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The eye that saw him will see  him no more,Nor will his place behold
        him anymore.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: His children will seek the favor of the poor,And his hands will restore
        his wealth.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: His bones are full of his youthful vigor,But it will lie down with
        him in the dust.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThough evil is sweet in his mouth,And he hides it under his
        tongue,"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Though he spares it and does not forsake it,But still keeps it in
        his mouth,
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Yet his food in his stomach turns sour;It becomes cobra venom within
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He swallows down richesAnd vomits them up again;God casts them out
        of his belly.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He will suck the poison of cobras;The viper\u2019s tongue will slay
        him."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He will not see the streams,The rivers flowing with honey and cream.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He will restore that for which he labored,And will not swallow it
        down;From the proceeds of businessHe will get no enjoyment.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: For he has oppressed and forsaken the poor,He has violently seized
        a house which he did not build.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBecause he knows no quietness in his heart,He will not save
        anything he desires."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Nothing is left for him to eat;Therefore his well-being will not last.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: In his self-sufficiency he will be in distress;Every hand of misery
        will come against him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: When he is about to fill his stomach,God will cast on him the fury
        of His wrath,And will rain it on him while he is eating.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He will flee from the iron weapon;A bronze bow will pierce him through.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: It is drawn, and comes out of the body;Yes, the glittering point 
        comes out of his gall.Terrors come upon him;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Total darkness is reserved for his treasures.An unfanned fire will
        consume him;It shall go ill with him who is left in his tent.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The heavens will reveal his iniquity,And the earth will rise up against
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The increase of his house will depart,And  his  goods will flow away
        in the day of His wrath.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "This is the portion from God for a wicked man,The heritage appointed
        to him by God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Discourse on the Wicked"
      title: "Job\u2019s Discourse on the Wicked"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CListen carefully to my speech,And let this be your consolation."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Bear with me that I may speak,And after I have spoken, keep mocking.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAs for me, is my complaint against man?And if it  were, why
        should I not be impatient?"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Look at me and be astonished;Put your hand over your mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Even when I remember I am terrified,And trembling takes hold of my
        flesh.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Why do the wicked live and become old,Yes, become mighty in power?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Their descendants are established with them in their sight,And their
        offspring before their eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Their houses are safe from fear,Neither is the rod of God upon them.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Their bull breeds without failure;Their cow calves without miscarriage.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: They send forth their little ones like a flock,And their children
        dance.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: They sing to the tambourine and harp,And rejoice to the sound of the
        flute.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: They spend their days in wealth,And in a moment go down to the grave.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Yet they say to God, \u2018Depart from us,For we do not desire the
        knowledge of Your ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Who is the Almighty, that we should serve Him?And what profit do
        we have if we pray to Him?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Indeed their prosperity is not in their hand;The counsel of the wicked
        is far from me.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CHow often is the lamp of the wicked put out?How  often does
        their destruction come upon them,The sorrows God  distributes in His anger?"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: They are like straw before the wind,And like chaff that a storm carries
        away.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They  say, \u2018God lays up one\u2019s iniquity for his children\u2019;Let
        Him recompense him, that he may know it."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Let his eyes see his destruction,And let him drink of the wrath of
        the Almighty.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For what does he care about his household after him,When the number
        of his months is cut in half?
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CCan  anyone teach God knowledge,Since He judges those on high?"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: One dies in his full strength,Being wholly at ease and secure;
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: His pails are full of milk,And the marrow of his bones is moist.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Another man dies in the bitterness of his soul,Never having eaten
        with pleasure.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: They lie down alike in the dust,And worms cover them.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CLook, I know your thoughts,And the schemes with  which you
        would wrong me."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For you say,\u2018Where is the house of the prince?And where is the
        tent,The dwelling place of the wicked?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Have you not asked those who travel the road?And do you not know their
        signs?
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: For the wicked are reserved for the day of doom;They shall be brought
        out on the day of wrath.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Who condemns his way to his face?And who repays him for  what he has
        done?
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Yet he shall be brought to the grave,And a vigil kept over the tomb.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: The clods of the valley shall be sweet to him;Everyone shall follow
        him,As countless have  gone before him.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "How then can you comfort me with empty words,Since falsehood remains
        in your answers?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Eliphaz Accuses Job of Wickedness'
      title: Eliphaz Accuses Job of Wickedness
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CCan a man be profitable to God,Though he who is wise may be
        profitable to himself?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Is  it any pleasure to the Almighty that you are righteous?Or is 
        it gain to  Him that you make your ways blameless?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIs it because of your fear of Him that He corrects you,And
        enters into judgment with you?"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Is not your wickedness great,And your iniquity without end?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For you have taken pledges from your brother for no reason,And stripped
        the naked of their clothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: You have not given the weary water to drink,And you have withheld
        bread from the hungry.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But the mighty man possessed the land,And the honorable man dwelt
        in it.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You have sent widows away empty,And the strength of the fatherless
        was crushed.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Therefore snares are all around you,And sudden fear troubles you,
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Or darkness so  that you cannot see;And an abundance of water covers
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIs not God in the height of heaven?And see the highest stars,
        how lofty they are!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And you say, \u2018What does God know?Can He judge through the deep
        darkness?"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thick clouds cover Him, so that He cannot see,And He walks above
        the circle of heaven.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Will you keep to the old wayWhich wicked men have trod,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Who were cut down before their time,Whose foundations were swept away
        by a flood?
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They said to God, \u2018Depart from us!What can the Almighty do to
        them?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Yet He filled their houses with good things;But the counsel of the
        wicked is far from me.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe righteous see it and are glad,And the innocent laugh at
        them:"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018Surely our adversaries are cut down,And the fire consumes their
        remnant.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CNow acquaint yourself with Him, and be at peace;Thereby good
        will come to you."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Receive, please, instruction from His mouth,And lay up His words in
        your heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: If you return to the Almighty, you will be built up;You will remove
        iniquity far from your tents.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Then you will lay your gold in the dust,And the gold of Ophir among
        the stones of the brooks.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Yes, the Almighty will be your goldAnd your precious silver;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For then you will have your delight in the Almighty,And lift up your
        face to God.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: You will make your prayer to Him,He will hear you,And you will pay
        your vows.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: You will also declare a thing,And it will be established for you;So
        light will shine on your ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When they cast you down, and you say, \u2018Exaltation will  come!\u2019Then
        He will save the humble person."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He will even deliver one who is not innocent;Yes, he will be delivered
        by the purity of your hands.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job Proclaims God\u2019s Righteous Judgments"
      title: "Job Proclaims God\u2019s Righteous Judgments"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CEven today my complaint is bitter;My hand is listless because
        of my groaning."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Oh, that I knew where I might find Him,That I might come to His seat!
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I would present my case before Him,And fill my mouth with arguments.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I would know the words which He would answer me,And understand what
        He would say to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Would He contend with me in His great power?No! But He would take
        note of me.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: There the upright could reason with Him,And I would be delivered forever
        from my Judge.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CLook, I go forward, but He is not there,And backward, but I
        cannot perceive Him;"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: When He works on the left hand, I cannot behold Him;When He turns
        to the right hand, I cannot see Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But He knows the way that I take;When  He has tested me, I shall come
        forth as gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: My foot has held fast to His steps;I have kept His way and not turned
        aside.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: I have not departed from the commandment of His lips;I have treasured
        the words of His mouthMore than my necessary food.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut He is unique, and who can make Him change?And whatever 
        His soul desires, that He does."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For He performs what  is  appointed for me,And many such things  are
        with Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Therefore I am terrified at His presence;When I consider this, I am
        afraid of Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For God made my heart weak,And the Almighty terrifies me;
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Because I was not cut off from the presence of darkness,And He did
        not hide deep darkness from my face.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Complains of Violence on the Earth'
      title: Job Complains of Violence on the Earth
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CSince  times are not hidden from the Almighty,Why do those
        who know Him see not His days?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSome remove landmarks;They seize flocks violently and feed
        on  them;"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They drive away the donkey of the fatherless;They take the widow\u2019s
        ox as a pledge."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They push the needy off the road;All the poor of the land are forced
        to hide.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Indeed, like wild donkeys in the desert,They go out to their work,
        searching for food.The wilderness yields food for them and for their children.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They gather their fodder in the fieldAnd glean in the vineyard of
        the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They spend the night naked, without clothing,And have no covering
        in the cold.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They are wet with the showers of the mountains,And huddle around the
        rock for want of shelter.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CSome snatch the fatherless from the breast,And take a pledge
        from the poor."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: They cause the  poor to go naked, without clothing;And they take away
        the sheaves from the hungry.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: They press out oil within their walls,And tread winepresses, yet suffer
        thirst.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The dying groan in the city,And the souls of the wounded cry out;Yet
        God does not charge them with wrong.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThere are those who rebel against the light;They do not know
        its waysNor abide in its paths."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The murderer rises with the light;He kills the poor and needy;And
        in the night he is like a thief.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The eye of the adulterer waits for the twilight,Saying, \u2018No
        eye will see me\u2019;And he disguises his face."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: In the dark they break into housesWhich they marked for themselves
        in the daytime;They do not know the light.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For the morning is the same to them as the shadow of death;If someone
        recognizes them,They  are  in the terrors of the shadow of death.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThey should  be swift on the face of the waters,Their portion
        should  be cursed in the earth,So  that no one  would turn into the way of
        their vineyards."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: As drought and heat consume the snow waters,So the grave consumes 
        those  who have sinned.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The womb should forget him,The worm should feed sweetly on him;He
        should be remembered no more,And wickedness should be broken like a tree.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For he preys on the barren who do not bear,And does no good for the
        widow.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CBut God draws the mighty away with His power;He rises up, but
        no man is sure of life."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He gives them security, and they rely on  it;Yet His eyes are on their
        ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: They are exalted for a little while,Then they are gone.They are brought
        low;They are taken out of the way like all others;They dry out like the heads
        of grain.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CNow if it  is not so, who will prove me a liar,And make my
        speech worth nothing?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bildad: How Can Man Be Righteous?'
      title: 'Bildad: How Can Man Be Righteous?'
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Bildad the Shuhite answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDominion and fear belong to Him;He makes peace in His high
        places."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Is there any number to His armies?Upon whom does His light not rise?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: How then can man be righteous before God?Or how can he be pure who 
        is born of a woman?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: If even the moon does not shine,And the stars are not pure in His
        sight,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "How much less man, who  is  a maggot,And a son of man, who  is a
        worm?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job: Man\u2019s Frailty and God\u2019s Majesty"
      title: "Job: Man\u2019s Frailty and God\u2019s Majesty"
      number: 1
      content: 'But Job answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHow have you helped him  who  is without power?How have you
        saved the arm that  has no strength?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: How have you counseled one  who  has no wisdom?And how have you declared
        sound advice to many?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: To whom have you uttered words?And whose spirit came from you?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThe dead tremble,Those under the waters and those inhabiting
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Sheol is naked before Him,And Destruction has no covering.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He stretches out the north over empty space;He hangs the earth on
        nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He binds up the water in His thick clouds,Yet the clouds are not broken
        under it.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He covers the face of His throne,And spreads His cloud over it.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He drew a circular horizon on the face of the waters,At the boundary
        of light and darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The pillars of heaven tremble,And are astonished at His rebuke.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He stirs up the sea with His power,And by His understanding He breaks
        up the storm.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: By His Spirit He adorned the heavens;His hand pierced the fleeing
        serpent.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Indeed these are the mere edges of His ways,And how small a whisper
        we hear of Him!But the thunder of His power who can understand?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Job Maintains His Integrity'
      title: Job Maintains His Integrity
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover Job continued his discourse, and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAs God lives, who has taken away my justice,And the Almighty,
        who has made my soul bitter,"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: As long as my breath is in me,And the breath of God in my nostrils,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: My lips will not speak wickedness,Nor my tongue utter deceit.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Far be it from meThat I should say you are right;Till I die I will
        not put away my integrity from me.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: My righteousness I hold fast, and will not let it go;My heart shall
        not reproach me as long as I live.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CMay my enemy be like the wicked,And he who rises up against
        me like the unrighteous."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For what is the hope of the hypocrite,Though he may gain much,If God
        takes away his life?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Will God hear his cryWhen trouble comes upon him?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Will he delight himself in the Almighty?Will he always call on God?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI will teach you about the hand of God;What is with the Almighty
        I will not conceal."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Surely all of you have seen it;Why then do you behave with complete
        nonsense?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThis is the portion of a wicked man with God,And the heritage
        of oppressors, received from the Almighty:"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: If his children are multiplied, it  is for the sword;And his offspring
        shall not be satisfied with bread.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Those who survive him shall be buried in death,And their widows shall
        not weep,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Though he heaps up silver like dust,And piles up clothing like clay\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He may pile it up, but the just will wear it,And the innocent will
        divide the silver.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He builds his house like a moth,Like a booth which a watchman makes.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The rich man will lie down,But not be gathered up;He opens his eyes,And
        he is  no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Terrors overtake him like a flood;A tempest steals him away in the
        night.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The east wind carries him away, and he is gone;It sweeps him out of
        his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: It hurls against him and does not spare;He flees desperately from
        its power.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Men shall clap their hands at him,And shall hiss him out of his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Discourse on Wisdom"
      title: "Job\u2019s Discourse on Wisdom"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CSurely there is a mine for silver,And a place where gold is
        refined."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Iron is taken from the earth,And copper is smelted from ore.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Man puts an end to darkness,And searches every recessFor ore in the
        darkness and the shadow of death.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: He breaks open a shaft away from people;In  places forgotten by feetThey
        hang far away from men;They swing to and fro.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: As  for the earth, from it comes bread,But underneath it is turned
        up as by fire;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Its stones are the source of sapphires,And it contains gold dust.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "That path no bird knows,Nor has the falcon\u2019s eye seen it."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The proud lions have not trodden it,Nor has the fierce lion passed
        over it.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He puts his hand on the flint;He overturns the mountains at the roots.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He cuts out channels in the rocks,And his eye sees every precious
        thing.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He dams up the streams from trickling;What  is hidden he brings forth
        to light.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut where can wisdom be found?And where is the place of understanding?"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Man does not know its value,Nor is it found in the land of the living.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The deep says, \u2018It is not in me\u2019;And the sea says, \u2018It
        is not with me.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: It cannot be purchased for gold,Nor can silver be weighed for its
        price.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: It cannot be valued in the gold of Ophir,In precious onyx or sapphire.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Neither gold nor crystal can equal it,Nor can it be exchanged for
        jewelry of fine gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: No mention shall be made of coral or quartz,For the price of wisdom
        is above rubies.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The topaz of Ethiopia cannot equal it,Nor can it be valued in pure
        gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFrom where then does wisdom come?And where is the place of
        understanding?"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: It is hidden from the eyes of all living,And concealed from the birds
        of the air.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Destruction and Death say,\u2018We have heard a report about it with
        our ears.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: God understands its way,And He knows its place.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: For He looks to the ends of the earth,And  sees under the whole heavens,
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: To establish a weight for the wind,And apportion the waters by measure.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: When He made a law for the rain,And a path for the thunderbolt,
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then He saw wisdom and declared it;He prepared it, indeed, He searched
        it out.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And to man He said,\u2018Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom,And
        to depart from evil is understanding.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Summary Defense"
      title: "Job\u2019s Summary Defense"
      number: 1
      content: 'Job further continued his discourse, and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COh, that I were as in months past,As in the days when God watched
        over me;"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: When His lamp shone upon my head,And  when by His light I walked through
        darkness;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Just as I was in the days of my prime,When the friendly counsel of
        God was over my tent;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: When the Almighty was yet with me,When my children were around me;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: When my steps were bathed with cream,And the rock poured out rivers
        of oil for me!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWhen I went out to the gate by the city,When I took my seat
        in the open square,"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The young men saw me and hid,And the aged arose and stood;
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The princes refrained from talking,And put their hand on their mouth;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The voice of nobles was hushed,And their tongue stuck to the roof
        of their mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: When the ear heard, then it blessed me,And when the eye saw, then
        it approved me;
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Because I delivered the poor who cried out,The fatherless and the 
        one  who had no helper.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The blessing of a perishing man came upon me,And I caused the widow\u2019s
        heart to sing for joy."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I put on righteousness, and it clothed me;My justice was like a robe
        and a turban.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I was  eyes to the blind,And I was feet to the lame.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I was a father to the poor,And I searched out the case that I did
        not know.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I broke the fangs of the wicked,And plucked the victim from his teeth.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThen I said, \u2018I shall die in my nest,And multiply my days
        as the sand."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: My root is spread out to the waters,And the dew lies all night on
        my branch.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "My glory is fresh within me,And my bow is renewed in my hand.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CMen listened to me and waited,And kept silence for my counsel."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: After my words they did not speak again,And my speech settled on them
        as  dew.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: They waited for me as for the rain,And they opened their mouth wide
        as for the spring rain.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: If I mocked at them, they did not believe it,And the light of my countenance
        they did not cast down.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: I chose the way for them, and sat as chief;So I dwelt as a king in
        the army,As one who comforts mourners.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBut now they mock at me, men younger than I,Whose fathers I
        disdained to put with the dogs of my flock."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Indeed, what profit is the strength of their hands to me?Their vigor
        has perished.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: They  are gaunt from want and famine,Fleeing late to the wilderness,
        desolate and waste,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Who pluck mallow by the bushes,And broom tree roots for their food.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: They were driven out from among men,They shouted at them as at a thief.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They  had to live in the clefts of the valleys,In caves of the earth
        and the rocks.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Among the bushes they brayed,Under the nettles they nestled.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They  were sons of fools,Yes, sons of vile men;They were scourged
        from the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd now I am their taunting song;Yes, I am their byword."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: They abhor me, they keep far from me;They do not hesitate to spit
        in my face.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Because He has loosed my bowstring and afflicted me,They have cast
        off restraint before me.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: At my right hand the rabble arises;They push away my feet,And they
        raise against me their ways of destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: They break up my path,They promote my calamity;They have no helper.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They come as broad breakers;Under the ruinous storm they roll along.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Terrors are turned upon me;They pursue my honor as the wind,And my
        prosperity has passed like a cloud.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd now my soul is poured out because of my plight;The days
        of affliction take hold of me."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: My bones are pierced in me at night,And my gnawing pains take no rest.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: By great force my garment is disfigured;It binds me about as the collar
        of my coat.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He has cast me into the mire,And I have become like dust and ashes.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CI cry out to You, but You do not answer me;I stand up, and
        You regard me."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But You have become cruel to me;With the strength of Your hand You
        oppose me.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: You lift me up to the wind and cause me to ride on  it;You spoil my
        success.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For I know that You will bring me to death,And to the house appointed
        for all living.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSurely He would not stretch out His hand against a heap of
        ruins,If they cry out when He destroys it."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Have I not wept for him who was in trouble?Has not my soul grieved
        for the poor?
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: But when I looked for good, evil came to  me;And when I waited for
        light, then came darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: My heart is in turmoil and cannot rest;Days of affliction confront
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: I go about mourning, but not in the sun;I stand up in the assembly
        and cry out for help.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: I am a brother of jackals,And a companion of ostriches.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: My skin grows black and falls from me;My bones burn with fever.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: My harp is turned to mourning,And my flute to the voice of those who
        weep.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CI have made a covenant with my eyes;Why then should I look
        upon a young woman?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For what is the allotment of God from above,And the inheritance of
        the Almighty from on high?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Is it not destruction for the wicked,And disaster for the workers
        of iniquity?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Does He not see my ways,And count all my steps?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf I have walked with falsehood,Or if my foot has hastened
        to deceit,"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Let me be weighed on honest scales,That God may know my integrity.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: If my step has turned from the way,Or my heart walked after my eyes,Or
        if any spot adheres to my hands,
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then  let me sow, and another eat;Yes, let my harvest be rooted out.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIf my heart has been enticed by a woman,Or if I have lurked
        at my neighbor\u2019s door,"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then let my wife grind for another,And let others bow down over her.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For that would  be wickedness;Yes, it would  be iniquity deserving 
        of judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: For that would  be a fire that consumes to destruction,And would root
        out all my increase.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf I have despised the cause of my male or female servantWhen
        they complained against me,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: What then shall I do when God rises up?When He punishes, how shall
        I answer Him?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Did not He who made me in the womb make them?Did not the same One
        fashion us in the womb?
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf I have kept the poor from their desire,Or caused the eyes
        of the widow to fail,"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Or eaten my morsel by myself,So that the fatherless could not eat
        of it
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "(But from my youth I reared him as a father,And from my mother\u2019s
        womb I guided the  widow);"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: If I have seen anyone perish for lack of clothing,Or any poor man
        without covering;
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: If his heart has not blessed me,And if he was not warmed with the
        fleece of my sheep;
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: If I have raised my hand against the fatherless,When I saw I had help
        in the gate;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then let my arm fall from my shoulder,Let my arm be torn from the
        socket.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For destruction from God is a terror to me,And because of His magnificence
        I cannot endure.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CIf I have made gold my hope,Or said to fine gold, \u2018You 
        are my confidence\u2019;"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: If I have rejoiced because my wealth was great,And because my hand
        had gained much;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: If I have observed the sun when it shines,Or the moon moving in brightness,
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: So that my heart has been secretly enticed,And my mouth has kissed
        my hand;
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: This also would  be an iniquity deserving  of judgment,For I would
        have denied God who  is above.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIf I have rejoiced at the destruction of him who hated me,Or
        lifted myself up when evil found him"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: (Indeed I have not allowed my mouth to sinBy asking for a curse on
        his soul);
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "If the men of my tent have not said,\u2018Who is there that has not
        been satisfied with his meat?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: (But no sojourner had to lodge in the street,For I have opened my
        doors to the traveler);
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: If I have covered my transgressions as Adam,By hiding my iniquity
        in my bosom,
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Because I feared the great multitude,And dreaded the contempt of
        families,So that I kept silenceAnd did not go out of the door\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Oh, that I had one to hear me!Here is my mark.Oh, that the Almighty
        would answer me,That my Prosecutor had written a book!
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Surely I would carry it on my shoulder,And bind it on me like a crown;
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: I would declare to Him the number of my steps;Like a prince I would
        approach Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CIf my land cries out against me,And its furrows weep together;"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: If I have eaten its fruit without money,Or caused its owners to lose
        their lives;
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then let thistles grow instead of wheat,And weeds instead of barley.\u201DThe
        words of Job are ended."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Contradicts Job\u2019s Friends"
      title: "Elihu Contradicts Job\u2019s Friends"
      number: 1
      content: 'So these three men ceased answering Job, because he was  righteous
        in his own eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the wrath of Elihu, the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the family
        of Ram, was aroused against Job; his wrath was aroused because he justified
        himself rather than God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Also against his three friends his wrath was aroused, because they
        had found no answer, and yet had condemned Job.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now because they were years older than he, Elihu had waited to speak
        to Job. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: When Elihu saw that there  was no answer in the mouth of these three
        men, his wrath was aroused.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Elihu, the son of Barachel the Buzite, answered and said:\u201CI
        am  young in years, and you are very old;Therefore I was afraid,And dared
        not declare my opinion to you."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I said, \u2018Age should speak,And multitude of years should teach
        wisdom.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But there  is a spirit in man,And the breath of the Almighty gives
        him understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Great men are not always wise,Nor do the aged always understand justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore I say, \u2018Listen to me,I also will declare my
        opinion.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Indeed I waited for your words,I listened to your reasonings, while
        you searched out what to say.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I paid close attention to you;And surely not one of you convinced
        Job,Or answered his words\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Lest you say,\u2018We have found wisdom\u2019;God will vanquish him,
        not man."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Now he has not directed his words against me;So I will not answer
        him with your words.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThey are dismayed and answer no more;Words escape them."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And I have waited, because they did not speak,Because they stood still
        and answered no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I also will answer my part,I too will declare my opinion.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For I am full of words;The spirit within me compels me.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Indeed my belly is like wine that has no vent;It is ready to burst
        like new wineskins.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: I will speak, that I may find relief;I must open my lips and answer.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Let me not, I pray, show partiality to anyone;Nor let me flatter any
        man.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For I do not know how to flatter,Else my Maker would soon take me
        away.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Contradicts Job'
      title: Elihu Contradicts Job
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBut please, Job, hear my speech,And listen to all my words."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Now, I open my mouth;My tongue speaks in my mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: My words come from my upright heart;My lips utter pure knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The Spirit of God has made me,And the breath of the Almighty gives
        me life.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: If you can answer me,Set your  words in order before me;Take your
        stand.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Truly I am as your spokesman before God;I also have been formed out
        of clay.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Surely no fear of me will terrify you,Nor will my hand be heavy on
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CSurely you have spoken in my hearing,And I have heard the sound
        of your words, saying,"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018I  am pure, without transgression;I am innocent, and there 
        is no iniquity in me."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Yet He finds occasions against me,He counts me as His enemy;
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He puts my feet in the stocks,He watches all my paths.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CLook, in this you are not righteous.I will answer you,For God
        is greater than man."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Why do you contend with Him?For He does not give an accounting of
        any of His words.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For God may speak in one way, or in another,Yet  man does not perceive
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: In a dream, in a vision of the night,When deep sleep falls upon men,While
        slumbering on their beds,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Then He opens the ears of men,And seals their instruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: In order to turn man from  his deed,And conceal pride from man,
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: He keeps back his soul from the Pit,And his life from perishing by
        the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CMan is also chastened with pain on his bed,And with strong
        pain in many of his bones,"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So that his life abhors bread,And his soul succulent food.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: His flesh wastes away from sight,And his bones stick out which  once
        were not seen.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Yes, his soul draws near the Pit,And his life to the executioners.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CIf there is a messenger for him,A mediator, one among a thousand,To
        show man His uprightness,"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then He is gracious to him, and says,\u2018Deliver him from going
        down to the Pit;I have found a ransom\u2019;"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "His flesh shall be young like a child\u2019s,He shall return to the
        days of his youth."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He shall pray to God, and He will delight in him,He shall see His
        face with joy,For He restores to man His righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then he looks at men and says,\u2018I have sinned, and perverted
        what  was right,And it did not profit me.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: He will redeem his soul from going down to the Pit,And his life shall
        see the light.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CBehold, God works all these things,Twice, in  fact, three times
        with a man,"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: To bring back his soul from the Pit,That he may be enlightened with
        the light of life.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CGive ear, Job, listen to me;Hold your peace, and I will speak."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: If you have anything to say, answer me;Speak, for I desire to justify
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "If not, listen to me;Hold your peace, and I will teach you wisdom.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Justice"
      title: "Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Justice"
      number: 1
      content: 'Elihu further answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear my words, you wise men;Give ear to me, you who have knowledge."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For the ear tests wordsAs the palate tastes food.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Let us choose justice for ourselves;Let us know among ourselves what
        is good.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor Job has said, \u2018I am righteous,But God has taken away
        my justice;"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Should I lie concerning my right?My wound is incurable, though  I 
        am without transgression.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: What man is like Job,Who drinks scorn like water,
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Who goes in company with the workers of iniquity,And walks with wicked
        men?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For he has said, \u2018It profits a man nothingThat he should delight
        in God.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTherefore listen to me, you men of understanding:Far be it
        from God to  do wickedness,And from the Almighty to commit iniquity."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For He repays man according  to his work,And makes man to find a reward
        according to his way.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Surely God will never do wickedly,Nor will the Almighty pervert justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Who gave Him charge over the earth?Or who appointed Him  over the
        whole world?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: If He should set His heart on it,If He should gather to Himself His
        Spirit and His breath,
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: All flesh would perish together,And man would return to dust.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf you  have understanding, hear this;Listen to the sound of
        my words:"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Should one who hates justice govern?Will you condemn Him  who  is
        most just?
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Is  it  fitting to say to a king, \u2018You  are worthless,\u2019And
        to nobles, \u2018You  are wicked\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Yet He is not partial to princes,Nor does He regard the rich more
        than the poor;For they are all the work of His hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: In a moment they die, in the middle of the night;The people are shaken
        and pass away;The mighty are taken away without a hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CFor His eyes are on the ways of man,And He sees all his steps."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: There is no darkness nor shadow of deathWhere the workers of iniquity
        may hide themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For He need not further consider a man,That he should go before God
        in judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He breaks in pieces mighty men without inquiry,And sets others in
        their place.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Therefore He knows their works;He overthrows them in the night,And
        they are crushed.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He strikes them as wicked menIn the open sight of others,
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Because they turned back from Him,And would not consider any of His
        ways,
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So that they caused the cry of the poor to come to Him;For He hears
        the cry of the afflicted.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When He gives quietness, who then can make trouble?And when He hides
        His face, who then can see Him,Whether it  is against a nation or a man alone?\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: That the hypocrite should not reign,Lest the people be ensnared.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CFor has anyone said to God,\u2018I have borne chastening;I
        will offend no more;"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Teach me what I do not see;If I have done iniquity, I will do no
        more\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Should He repay it according to your terms,Just because you disavow
        it?You must choose, and not I;Therefore speak what you know.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CMen of understanding say to me,Wise men who listen to me:"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018Job speaks without knowledge,His words are without wisdom.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Oh, that Job were tried to the utmost,Because his answers are  like
        those of wicked men!
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For he adds rebellion to his sin;He claps his  hands among us,And
        multiplies his words against God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elihu Condemns Self-Righteousness'
      title: Elihu Condemns Self-Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover Elihu answered and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDo you think this is right?Do you say,\u2018My righteousness
        is more than God\u2019s\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For you say,\u2018What advantage will it be to You?What profit shall
        I have, more than if I had sinned?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will answer you,And your companions with you."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Look to the heavens and see;And behold the clouds\u2014They are higher
        than you."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: If you sin, what do you accomplish against Him?Or, if your transgressions
        are multiplied, what do you do to Him?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: If you are righteous, what do you give Him?Or what does He receive
        from your hand?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Your wickedness affects a man such as you,And your righteousness a
        son of man.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBecause of the multitude of oppressions they cry out;They cry
        out for help because of the arm of the mighty."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But no one says, \u2018Where is God my Maker,Who gives songs in the
        night,"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Who teaches us more than the beasts of the earth,And makes us wiser
        than the birds of heaven?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: There they cry out, but He does not answer,Because of the pride of
        evil men.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Surely God will not listen to empty talk,Nor will the Almighty regard
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Although you say you do not see Him,Yet justice is before Him, and
        you must wait for Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And now, because He has not punished in His anger,Nor taken much notice
        of folly,
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore Job opens his mouth in vain;He multiplies words without
        knowledge.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Goodness"
      title: "Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Goodness"
      number: 1
      content: 'Elihu also proceeded and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBear with me a little, and I will show youThat there  are yet
        words to speak on God\u2019s behalf."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I will fetch my knowledge from afar;I will ascribe righteousness to
        my Maker.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For truly my words are not false;One who is perfect in knowledge is
        with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBehold, God is mighty, but despises no  one;He  is mighty in
        strength of understanding."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He does not preserve the life of the wicked,But gives justice to the
        oppressed.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He does not withdraw His eyes from the righteous;But they  are on
        the throne with kings,For He has seated them forever,And they are exalted.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And if they  are bound in fetters,Held in the cords of affliction,
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then He tells them their work and their transgressions\u2014That
        they have acted defiantly."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He also opens their ear to instruction,And commands that they turn
        from iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: If they obey and serve Him,They shall spend their days in prosperity,And
        their years in pleasures.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: But if they do not obey,They shall perish by the sword,And they shall
        die without knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut the hypocrites in heart store up wrath;They do not cry
        for help when He binds them."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They die in youth,And their life ends among the perverted persons.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He delivers the poor in their affliction,And opens their ears in oppression.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIndeed He would have brought you out of dire distress,Into
        a broad place where there  is no restraint;And what is set on your table
        would  be full of richness."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But you are filled with the judgment due the wicked;Judgment and justice
        take hold of  you.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Because there  is wrath, beware lest He take you away with one blow;For
        a large ransom would not help you avoid it.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Will your riches,Or all the mighty forces,Keep you from distress?
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Do not desire the night,When people are cut off in their place.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Take heed, do not turn to iniquity,For you have chosen this rather
        than affliction.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CBehold, God is exalted by His power;Who teaches like Him?"
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Majesty"
      title: "Elihu Proclaims God\u2019s Majesty"
      number: 23
      content: "Who has assigned Him His way,Or who has said, \u2018You have done
        wrong\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CRemember to magnify His work,Of which men have sung."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Everyone has seen it;Man looks on it from afar.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBehold, God is great, and we do not know Him;Nor can the number
        of His years be discovered."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For He draws up drops of water,Which distill as rain from the mist,
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Which the clouds drop downAnd pour abundantly on man.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Indeed, can anyone understand the spreading of clouds,The thunder
        from His canopy?
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Look, He scatters His light upon it,And covers the depths of the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: For by these He judges the peoples;He gives food in abundance.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: He covers His hands with lightning,And commands it to strike.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: His thunder declares it,The cattle also, concerning the rising storm.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAt this also my heart trembles,And leaps from its place."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Hear attentively the thunder of His voice,And the rumbling that comes
        from His mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He sends it forth under the whole heaven,His lightning to the ends
        of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: After it a voice roars;He thunders with His majestic voice,And He
        does not restrain them when His voice is heard.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: God thunders marvelously with His voice;He does great things which
        we cannot comprehend.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For He says to the snow, \u2018Fall on the earth\u2019;Likewise to
        the gentle rain and the heavy rain of His strength."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He seals the hand of every man,That all men may know His work.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The beasts go into dens,And remain in their lairs.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: From the chamber of  the  south comes the whirlwind,And cold from
        the scattering winds of  the  north.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: By the breath of God ice is given,And the broad waters are frozen.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Also with moisture He saturates the thick clouds;He scatters His bright
        clouds.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And they swirl about, being turned by His guidance,That they may do
        whatever He commands themOn the face of the whole earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He causes it to come,Whether for correction,Or for His land,Or for
        mercy.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CListen to this, O Job;Stand still and consider the wondrous
        works of God."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Do you know when God dispatches them,And causes the light of His cloud
        to shine?
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Do you know how the clouds are balanced,Those wondrous works of Him
        who is perfect in knowledge?
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Why are your garments hot,When He quiets the earth by the south wind?
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: With Him, have you spread out the skies,Strong as a cast metal mirror?
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CTeach us what we should say to Him,For we can prepare nothing
        because of the darkness."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Should He be told that I wish  to speak?If a man were to speak, surely
        he would be swallowed up.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Even now men cannot look at the light when  it  is bright in the skies,When
        the wind has passed and cleared them.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He comes from the north as golden splendor;With God is awesome majesty.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: As  for the Almighty, we cannot find Him;He  is excellent in power,In
        judgment and abundant justice;He does not oppress.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore men fear Him;He shows no partiality to any who  are  wise
        of heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lord Reveals His Omnipotence to Job'
      title: The Lord Reveals His Omnipotence to Job
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind, and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWho  is this who darkens counselBy words without knowledge?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Now prepare yourself like a man;I will question you, and you shall
        answer Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhere were you when I laid the foundations of the earth?Tell
        Me, if you have understanding."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Who determined its measurements?Surely you know!Or who stretched the
        line upon it?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: To what were its foundations fastened?Or who laid its cornerstone,
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: When the morning stars sang together,And all the sons of God shouted
        for joy?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201COr  who shut in the sea with doors,When it burst forth and
        issued from the womb;"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: When I made the clouds its garment,And thick darkness its swaddling
        band;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When I fixed My limit for it,And set bars and doors;
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When I said,\u2018This far you may come, but no farther,And here
        your proud waves must stop!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHave you commanded the morning since your days began,And caused
        the dawn to know its place,"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: That it might take hold of the ends of the earth,And the wicked be
        shaken out of it?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: It takes on form like clay under a seal,And stands out like a garment.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: From the wicked their light is withheld,And the upraised arm is broken.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CHave you entered the springs of the sea?Or have you walked
        in search of the depths?"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Have the gates of death been revealed to you?Or have you seen the
        doors of the shadow of death?
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Have you comprehended the breadth of the earth?Tell Me, if you know
        all this.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhere is the way to the dwelling of light?And darkness, where
        is its place,"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: That you may take it to its territory,That you may know the paths
        to its home?
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Do you know it, because you were born then,Or because the number of
        your days is great?
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CHave you entered the treasury of snow,Or have you seen the
        treasury of hail,"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Which I have reserved for the time of trouble,For the day of battle
        and war?
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: By what way is light diffused,Or the east wind scattered over the
        earth?
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CWho has divided a channel for the overflowing water,Or a path
        for the thunderbolt,"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: To cause it to rain on a land where  there  is no one,A wilderness
        in which there  is no man;
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: To satisfy the desolate waste,And cause to spring forth the growth
        of tender grass?
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Has the rain a father?Or who has begotten the drops of dew?
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: From whose womb comes the ice?And the frost of heaven, who gives it
        birth?
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The waters harden like stone,And the surface of the deep is frozen.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CCan you bind the cluster of the Pleiades,Or loose the belt
        of Orion?"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Can you bring out Mazzaroth in its season?Or can you guide the Great
        Bear with its cubs?
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Do you know the ordinances of the heavens?Can you set their dominion
        over the earth?
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CCan you lift up your voice to the clouds,That an abundance
        of water may cover you?"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Can you send out lightnings, that they may go,And say to you, \u2018Here
        we are!\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Who has put wisdom in the mind?Or who has given understanding to the
        heart?
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Who can number the clouds by wisdom?Or who can pour out the bottles
        of heaven,
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: When the dust hardens in clumps,And the clods cling together?
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CCan you hunt the prey for the lion,Or satisfy the appetite
        of the young lions,"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: When they crouch in their dens,Or lurk in their lairs to lie in wait?
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: Who provides food for the raven,When its young ones cry to God,And
        wander about for lack of food?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CDo you know the time when the wild mountain goats bear young?Or
        can you mark when the deer gives birth?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Can you number the months that they fulfill?Or do you know the time
        when they bear young?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: They bow down,They bring forth their young,They deliver their offspring.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Their young ones are healthy,They grow strong with grain;They depart
        and do not return to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWho set the wild donkey free?Who loosed the bonds of the onager,"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Whose home I have made the wilderness,And the barren land his dwelling?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He scorns the tumult of the city;He does not heed the shouts of the
        driver.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The range of the mountains is his pasture,And he searches after every
        green thing.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWill the wild ox be willing to serve you?Will he bed by your
        manger?"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Can you bind the wild ox in the furrow with ropes?Or will he plow
        the valleys behind you?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Will you trust him because his strength is great?Or will you leave
        your labor to him?
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Will you trust him to bring home your grain,And gather it to your
        threshing floor?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThe wings of the ostrich wave proudly,But are her wings and
        pinions like  the kindly stork\u2019s?"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For she leaves her eggs on the ground,And warms them in the dust;
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: She forgets that a foot may crush them,Or that a wild beast may break
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: She treats her young harshly, as though they  were not hers;Her labor
        is in vain, without concern,
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Because God deprived her of wisdom,And did not endow her with understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: When she lifts herself on high,She scorns the horse and its rider.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CHave you given the horse strength?Have you clothed his neck
        with thunder?"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Can you frighten him like a locust?His majestic snorting strikes terror.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He paws in the valley, and rejoices in his strength;He gallops into
        the clash of arms.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He mocks at fear, and is not frightened;Nor does he turn back from
        the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The quiver rattles against him,The glittering spear and javelin.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He devours the distance with fierceness and rage;Nor does he come
        to a halt because the trumpet has sounded.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "At the  blast  of the trumpet he says, \u2018Aha!\u2019He smells
        the battle from afar,The thunder of captains and shouting."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CDoes the hawk fly by your wisdom,And spread its wings toward
        the south?"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Does the eagle mount up at your command,And make its nest on high?
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: On the rock it dwells and resides,On the crag of the rock and the
        stronghold.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: From there it spies out the prey;Its eyes observe from afar.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Its young ones suck up blood;And where the slain are, there it is.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover the Lord  answered Job, and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: "2: Job\u2019s Response to God"
      title: "Job\u2019s Response to God"
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CShall the one who contends with the Almighty correct Him?He
        who rebukes God, let him answer it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Job answered the Lord and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am vile;What shall I answer You?I lay my hand over
        my mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: "5: God\u2019s Challenge to Job"
      title: "God\u2019s Challenge to Job"
      number: 5
      content: "Once I have spoken, but I will not answer;Yes, twice, but I will
        proceed no further.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind, and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CNow prepare yourself like a man;I will question you, and you
        shall answer Me:"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWould you indeed annul My judgment?Would you condemn Me that
        you may be justified?"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Have you an arm like God?Or can you thunder with a voice like His?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then adorn yourself with majesty and splendor,And array yourself with
        glory and beauty.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Disperse the rage of your wrath;Look on everyone who  is proud, and
        humble him.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Look on everyone who  is  proud, and bring him low;Tread down the
        wicked in their place.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Hide them in the dust together,Bind their faces in hidden darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then I will also confess to youThat your own right hand can save you.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CLook now at the behemoth, which I made along with you;He eats
        grass like an ox."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: See now, his strength is in his hips,And his power is in his stomach
        muscles.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He moves his tail like a cedar;The sinews of his thighs are tightly
        knit.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: His bones are  like beams of bronze,His ribs like bars of iron.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He is the first of the ways of God;Only He who made him can bring
        near His sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Surely the mountains yield food for him,And all the beasts of the
        field play there.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He lies under the lotus trees,In a covert of reeds and marsh.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The lotus trees cover him with their shade;The willows by the brook
        surround him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Indeed the river may rage,Yet he is not disturbed;He is confident,
        though the Jordan gushes into his mouth,
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Though he takes it in his eyes,Or one pierces his nose with a snare.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CCan you draw out Leviathan with a hook,Or snare his tongue
        with a line which you lower?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Can you put a reed through his nose,Or pierce his jaw with a hook?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Will he make many supplications to you?Will he speak softly to you?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Will he make a covenant with you?Will you take him as a servant forever?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Will you play with him as with a bird,Or will you leash him for your
        maidens?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Will your companions make a banquet of him?Will they apportion him
        among the merchants?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Can you fill his skin with harpoons,Or his head with fishing spears?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Lay your hand on him;Remember the battle\u2014Never do it again!"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Indeed, any hope of overcoming him is false;Shall one  not be overwhelmed
        at the sight of him?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: No one is  so fierce that he would dare stir him up.Who then is able
        to stand against Me?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Who has preceded Me, that I should pay him?Everything under heaven
        is Mine.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI will not conceal his limbs,His mighty power, or his graceful
        proportions."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Who can remove his outer coat?Who can approach him with a double bridle?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Who can open the doors of his face,With his terrible teeth all around?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: His rows of scales are his pride,Shut up tightly as  with a seal;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: One is so near anotherThat no air can come between them;
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: They are joined one to another,They stick together and cannot be parted.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: His sneezings flash forth light,And his eyes are like the eyelids
        of the morning.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Out of his mouth go burning lights;Sparks of fire shoot out.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Smoke goes out of his nostrils,As from a boiling pot and burning rushes.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: His breath kindles coals,And a flame goes out of his mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Strength dwells in his neck,And sorrow dances before him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The folds of his flesh are joined together;They are firm on him and
        cannot be moved.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: His heart is as hard as stone,Even as hard as the lower millstone.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: When he raises himself up, the mighty are afraid;Because of his crashings
        they are beside themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Though the sword reaches him, it cannot avail;Nor does spear, dart,
        or javelin.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: He regards iron as straw,And bronze as rotten wood.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The arrow cannot make him flee;Slingstones become like stubble to
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Darts are regarded as straw;He laughs at the threat of javelins.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: His undersides are like sharp potsherds;He spreads pointed marks in
        the mire.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: He makes the deep boil like a pot;He makes the sea like a pot of ointment.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: He leaves a shining wake behind him;One would think the deep had white
        hair.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: On earth there is nothing like him,Which is made without fear.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He beholds every high thing;He is king over all the children of pride.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Job\u2019s Repentance and Restoration"
      title: "Job\u2019s Repentance and Restoration"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Job answered the Lord and said:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI know that You can do everything,And that no purpose of  Yours
        can be withheld from You."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You  asked,  \u2018Who is this who hides counsel without knowledge?\u2019Therefore
        I have uttered what I did not understand,Things too wonderful for me, which
        I did not know."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Listen, please, and let me speak;You  said,  \u2018I will question
        you, and you shall answer Me.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI have heard of You by the hearing of the ear,But now my eye
        sees You."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore I abhor myself,And repent in dust and ashes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And so it was, after the Lord had spoken these words to Job, that
        the Lord said to Eliphaz the Temanite, \u201CMy wrath is aroused against
        you and your two friends, for you have not spoken of Me what  is right, as
        My servant Job has.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now therefore, take for yourselves seven bulls and seven rams, go
        to My servant Job, and offer up for yourselves a burnt offering; and My servant
        Job shall pray for you. For I will accept him, lest I deal with you according 
        to  your folly; because you have not spoken of Me what  is right, as My servant
        Job has.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Eliphaz the Temanite and Bildad the Shuhite and Zophar the Naamathite
        went and did as the Lord commanded them; for the Lord had accepted Job. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the Lord restored Job\u2019s losses when he prayed for his friends.
        Indeed the Lord gave Job twice as much as he had before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then all his brothers, all his sisters, and all those who had been
        his acquaintances before, came to him and ate food with him in his house;
        and they consoled him and comforted him for all the adversity that the Lord
        had brought upon him. Each one gave him a piece of silver and each a ring
        of gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the Lord blessed the latter days of Job more than his beginning;
        for he had fourteen thousand sheep, six thousand camels, one thousand yoke
        of oxen, and one thousand female donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He also had seven sons and three daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he called the name of the first Jemimah, the name of the second
        Keziah, and the name of the third Keren-Happuch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: In all the land were found no women so beautiful as the daughters
        of Job; and their father gave them an inheritance among their brothers.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'After this Job lived one hundred and forty years, and saw his children
        and grandchildren for four generations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So Job died, old and full of days.
      comments: []
